Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_ldb(25.10)                                              write_ldb(25.10)

Name
       write_ldb  -  Converts  text  library  to Cadence binary format library
       called LDB

Syntax
       write_ldb

       -library <string >< >

       -outfile <string >< >

       Converts text library to Cadence binary format library called LDB.

       You can use LDB to run timing analysis. The ECSM and CCS libraries  can
       be  very large and loading them may take significant time. You can con-
       vert the ASCII NLDM (Liberty .lib), ECSM, and CCS libraries to  LDB  by
       using the write_ldb command.

       When  loading  the design, the timing libraries will be read faster be-
       cause the software reads the binary versions.

       Instead of the original ASCII libraries, you can  specify  LDB  in  the
       create_library_set command in MMMC configuration file.

       Notes:

              * The software generated LDB files can be used in Tempus.

              * LDB  files generated from Tempus can be used as input by other
                tools - Innovus, Genus, and Voltus.

              * LDB files are not forward compatible, that is, the LDB  gener-
                ated  from 15.2 version cannot be used with 15.1 or prior ver-
                sions of the software.

              * The software does not  support  concatenated  Liberty  library
                (multiple  libraries in the same dotlib file) files during LDB
                conversion. To use these files, you are required  to  separate
                out  individual  libraries before converting to individual LDB
                files.

Parameters
       -library <string >
              Specifies the name of the input library file.

       -outfile <string >
              Specifies the name of the generated LDB file.

Examples
              * The following example illustrates the conversion of  libraries
                to LDB:

                write_ldb -library A.lib -outfile A.ldb

Related Information
              * check_ldb_version

